// ============================================================================
// Example: Complex Formulas Combining Multiple Features
// ============================================================================
// Demonstrates:
//   - Quantifiers (forall, exists) with operators
//   - Subscripts and superscripts in formulas
//   - Comparison operators (<, >, <=, >=)
//   - Set operators (in, subset, union, intersect)
//   - EQUIV: blocks for equivalence chains
//
// Features:
//   - Combining propositional logic with quantifiers
//   - Mathematical notation in propositions
//   - Truth tables integrated with complex formulas
//
// See: docs/USER_GUIDE.md - Sections "Propositional Logic", "Predicate Logic"
// ============================================================================

=== Phase 3: Quantifiers and Mathematical Notation ===

** Example 1: Quantifiers **

(a)
forall x : N | x >= 0

(b)
exists y : N | y = 0

(c)
forall n : N | n >= 0 and n < 100

** Example 2: Subscripts and Superscripts **

(a)
x^2

(b)
a_1

(c)
x_i^2

** Example 3: Comparison Operators **

(a)
x < 10

(b)
x >= 0 and x <= 100

(c)
y > 5 or y = 0

** Example 4: Set Operators **

(a)
x in N

(b)
A subset B

(c)
A union B intersect C

** Example 5: Complex Expressions **

(a) EQUIV:
forall x : N | x in N and x >= 0
forall x : N | x >= 0

(b)
forall i : N | a_i > 0 => a_i^2 > 0

(c) TRUTH TABLE:
p | q | p => q
T | T | T
T | F | F
F | T | T
F | F | T

